Crate root for `ctx-summarize`, the tool that walks a context tree bottom-up and regenerates `.ctx` leaf/aggregate summaries via an LLM agent. This file is just module declarations plus a design note; no logic lives here.

Architecture is layered and must stay that way: `cli` (argv/io) sits over `runner` (pure orchestration) which depends only on the `fs` and `agent` seams — new orchestration logic belongs in `runner`, not `cli`. Prompts are loaded from `prompts/` at runtime, not embedded as string constants in code; adding a new prompt means adding a file, not a `const`. Dynamic data must go only in the agent's user message, not baked into prompt files.

`intent.md` is explicitly never written by this tool — if a caller expects intent files to appear alongside `.ctx` files, that's handled elsewhere or not at all.

Modules: `cpath` (context-path helpers), `error` (crate error type), `agent`/`fs` (external seams, likely trait-based for testability), `runner`, `cli`. Check each module's own file for behavior details — this file carries no logic itself.